    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "languages": [
        "occ"
      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "breakRef",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A valid reference to a text-break locator object. If the type of boundary specified by the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakType"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "BreakChar"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", you can pass "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NULL"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". You use the function "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1390362-uccreatetextbreaklocator"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to obtain a text-break locator object reference. If non-"
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NULL"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", the text-break locator object must support the type of boundary specified in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakType"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "breakType",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A value of type "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCTextBreakType"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", with exactly one bit set to specify a single type of boundary to be located. Since support for finding character boundaries is locale-independent and built into the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " function, if you specify "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "BreakChar"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " as the type of boundary, then the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakRef"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter is ignored and may be "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NULL"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "options",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCTextBreakOptions"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value to specify the operation of the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " function. You can use text-break locator options to control some location-independent aspects of a text-boundary search. Note that if you do not specify any "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCTextBreakOptions"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " values, "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " searches forward, but assumes that the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "startOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value refers to the character preceding the offset rather than the one at the offset. This can result in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " returning an offset that is equal to the start offset. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "textPtr",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A pointer to the initial character of the Unicode string to search. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "textLength",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The total count of Unicode characters in the string to search. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "startOffset",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UniCharArrayOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value specifying the offset from which "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is to begin searching for the next text boundary of the type specified in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakType"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter. If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "startOffset == 0"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " then "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "kUCTextBreakLeadingEdgeMask"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " must be set in the options parameter; if "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "startOffset == textLength"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " then "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "kUCTextBreakLeadingEdgeMask"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " must not be set. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "breakOffset",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A pointer to a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UniCharArrayOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " value. On return, the value pointed to by the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter is set to the offset of the text boundary located by "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". In normal usage (when exactly one of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "kUCTextBreakLeadingEdgeMask"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "kUCTextBreakGoBackwardsMask"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " are set), the result returned in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is not equal to that supplied in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "startOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter unless an error occurs (and the function result is other than "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "noErr"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "). However, when "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "kUCTextBreakLeadingEdgeMask"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "kUCTextBreakGoBackwardsMask"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " are both set or both clear, the result produced in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "breakOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " can be equal to the value of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "startOffset"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A result code.  The text-break locator referenced by the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "breakRef"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " parameter must support the type of boundary specified in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "breakType"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " parameter; otherwise, the function returns "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "kUCTextBreakLocatorMissingType"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function starts from a specified offset in a text buffer, and then proceeds forward or backward (as requested) until it finds the next text boundary of a particular locale-specific type, using a given set of options. The different types of breaks or boundaries in a line of Unicode text can include"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Boundaries of characters (treating surrogate pairs as a single character). "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " Boundaries of character clusters. A cluster is a group of characters that should be treated as single text element for editing operations such as cursor movement. Typically this includes groups such as a base character followed by a sequence of combining characters, for example, a Hangul syllable represented as a sequence of conjoining jamo characters or an Indic consonant cluster. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " Boundaries of words. This can be used to determine what to highlight as the result of a double-click. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " Potential line break locations. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Finding boundaries of characters is a locale-independent operation, and support for it is built directly into the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UCFindTextBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function. If that is the only type of text boundary that you wish to locate, it is not necessary to call "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UCCreateTextBreakLocator"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and create a text-break locator object."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When finished with the text-break locator object, dispose it using the function  "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1390419-ucdisposetextbreaklocator"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
